00:36:48,140 --> 00:36:49,540
- Then why the hell
are you doing it?

990
00:36:49,541 --> 00:36:53,041
- Because it's my goddamn fault.

991
00:36:53,045 --> 00:36:55,845
<i>[soft music]</i>

992
00:36:55,847 --> 00:36:59,077
- No, Harvey, it's not.

993
00:36:59,084 --> 00:37:02,019
It's Mike's fault
just as much as it is yours.

994
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:04,090
- Then why should I be the one
to throw him under the bus?

995
00:37:04,091 --> 00:37:05,889
- Don't you get it?
I am not asking you

996
00:37:05,891 --> 00:37:07,191
to throw him under the bus.

997
00:37:07,192 --> 00:37:08,526
I am asking you

998
00:37:08,527 --> 00:37:10,157
to believe that the two of you

999
00:37:10,162 --> 00:37:12,697
are worthy
of being found innocent.

1000
00:37:12,698 --> 00:37:14,298
- And what if I can't do that?

1001
00:37:14,299 --> 00:37:16,069
- Then you can march yourself
down to Gibbs's office

1002
00:37:16,070 --> 00:37:18,398
in the morning
and turn yourself in.

1003
00:37:18,403 --> 00:37:20,303
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1004
00:37:20,305 --> 00:37:23,135
But I don't want you to do that.

1005
00:37:23,141 --> 00:37:25,309
- Why not?

1006
00:37:25,310 --> 00:37:29,180
- Because I think you're worthy.

1007
00:37:29,181 --> 00:37:30,981
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1008
00:37:30,983 --> 00:37:33,417
And I don't want to lose you.

1009
00:37:33,418 --> 00:37:41,418
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1010
00:37:43,295 --> 00:37:45,455
Harvey,

1011
00:37:45,464 --> 00:37:47,033
go to the courthouse
in the morning,

1012
00:37:47,034 --> 00:37:49,002
sit with Mike
until that verdict comes in,

1013
00:37:49,003 --> 00:37:51,571
and show him
that you have faith in him.

1014
00:37:51,572 --> 00:37:54,038
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1015
00:37:54,039 --> 00:37:56,439
Like I have faith in you.

1016
00:38:01,446 --> 00:38:01,676
.

1017
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:04,610
<i>[soft music]</i>

1018
00:38:04,616 --> 00:38:07,476
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1019
00:38:07,486 --> 00:38:10,546
[cell phone buzzing]

1020
00:38:14,192 --> 00:38:16,092
[cell phone beeps]

1021
00:38:16,094 --> 00:38:18,729
- Hello?

1022
00:38:18,730 --> 00:38:20,960
Yeah, this is him.

1023
00:38:22,901 --> 00:38:25,901
Yeah, yeah, I'll be right there.

1024
00:38:25,904 --> 00:38:28,406
- How's the jury back so early?

1025
00:38:28,407 --> 00:38:31,207
- Oh, it's not the jury.

1026
00:38:31,209 --> 00:38:33,209
It's the prosecutor
from the Diaz case.

1027
00:38:33,211 --> 00:38:36,211
He wants to talk.

1028
00:38:36,214 --> 00:38:38,516
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1029
00:38:38,517 --> 00:38:40,517
- [sighs]

1030
00:38:40,519 --> 00:38:44,849
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1031
00:38:44,856 --> 00:38:46,386
<i>- I may have hired a fraud,</i>

1032
00:38:46,391 --> 00:38:48,591
<i>but you're the one who had
the chance to turn him in,</i>

1033
00:38:48,593 --> 00:38:51,228
<i>and you used his secret to get
what you always wanted...</i>

1034
00:38:51,229 --> 00:38:52,629
- Mr. Litt...
<i>- So don't come in here...</i>

1035
00:38:52,631 --> 00:38:53,861
- I'm sorry to interrupt,

1036
00:38:53,865 --> 00:38:55,965
but your cousin Gertrude's
on the phone.

1037
00:38:55,967 --> 00:38:57,197
She said she needs to know

1038
00:38:57,202 --> 00:38:59,872
whether you found
that old mixed tape of hers.

1039
00:39:01,873 --> 00:39:04,642
- Tell her I didn't.

1040
00:39:04,643 --> 00:39:07,978
Tell her it
must have gotten thrown out,

1041
00:39:07,979 --> 00:39:11,609
and to never ask me
about it again.

1042
00:39:11,616 --> 00:39:13,976
- Good.
- What do you mean "good"?

1043
00:39:13,985 --> 00:39:16,145
- I been wanting to tell
Anita Gibbs to go to hell

1044
00:39:16,154 --> 00:39:19,323
since this whole thing started.

1045
00:39:19,324 --> 00:39:26,797
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1046
00:39:26,798 --> 00:39:28,998
- Mr. Ross,

1047
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:31,330
I'd like to make your client
an offer.

1048
00:39:31,336 --> 00:39:33,336
- We're listening.

1049
00:39:33,338 --> 00:39:35,068
- We don't want you, Mr. Diaz.

1050
00:39:35,073 --> 00:39:38,642
- You said you were just driving
the truck and I believe you,

1051
00:39:38,643 --> 00:39:40,043
and we already have
the two gentleman

1052
00:39:40,045 --> 00:39:41,335
who committed the actual felony.

1053
00:39:41,346 --> 00:39:44,776
So, all you have to do
is testify against them,

1054
00:39:44,783 --> 00:39:46,020
and you walk.
- What?

1055
00:39:46,021 --> 00:39:47,447
- Holy shit.
No jail time?

1056
00:39:47,452 --> 00:39:49,019
- No jail time.
- Okay that's enough.

1057
00:39:49,020 --> 00:39:50,520
I need a moment with my client.
- No, I don't need a moment.

1058
00:39:50,522 --> 00:39:52,356
I'll take it.
- Mr. Diaz, listen to me.

1059
00:39:52,357 --> 00:39:54,417
Testifying against your friends
may not seem like a big deal

1060
00:39:54,426 --> 00:39:56,126
right now, but it's something
you are gonna have to live with

1061
00:39:56,128 --> 00:39:58,328
for the rest of your life.
- I don't owe them anything,

1062
00:39:58,330 --> 00:40:00,330
and if I can get myself off,
that's what I'm gonna do.

1063
00:40:00,332 --> 00:40:01,532
- He's only offering you this

1064
00:40:01,533 --> 00:40:03,003
because he doesn't have
a case against you.

1065
00:40:03,004 --> 00:40:06,601
- He's a two-time loser.
I'll make a case against him.

1066
00:40:06,605 --> 00:40:09,265
- Mr. Diaz...

1067
00:40:09,274 --> 00:40:12,276
- Give me the pen.

1068
00:40:12,277 --> 00:40:15,246
- [exhales sharply]
You are making a huge mistake.

1069
00:40:15,247 --> 00:40:18,007
- Yeah, well, I don't think so,

1070
00:40:18,016 --> 00:40:19,976
and if you were in my shoes,
you'd do the exact same thing.

1071
00:40:19,985 --> 00:40:22,615
- I would never
send my friends to prison.

1072
00:40:22,621 --> 00:40:23,951
- Yeah, well,
they find me guilty,

1073
00:40:23,955 --> 00:40:26,915
they're gonna send my friends
to prison anyways.

1074
00:40:26,925 --> 00:40:29,925
<i>[dark alternative music]</i>

1075
00:40:29,928 --> 00:40:37,928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1076
00:40:52,083 --> 00:41:00,083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1077
00:41:02,661 --> 00:41:10,661
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1078
00:41:24,916 --> 00:41:32,916
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1079
00:41:50,342 --> 00:41:51,642
- Harvey, thank God.

1080
00:41:51,643 --> 00:41:53,943
The jury came back.
We have an hour.

1081
00:41:53,945 --> 00:41:57,475
- Where's Mike?
- I don't know.

1082
00:41:57,482 --> 00:41:59,082
- What's the matter?

1083
00:41:59,084 --> 00:42:00,451
Harvey?

1084
00:42:00,452 --> 00:42:01,782
- I have to go.

1085
00:42:01,786 --> 00:42:09,786
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1086
00:42:21,273 --> 00:42:29,273
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1087
00:42:37,055 --> 00:42:40,615
- You know they're back, right?
- I don't care.

1088
00:42:40,625 --> 00:42:42,925
- I'm ready to take your deal.

1089
00:42:42,928 --> 00:42:44,328
- Which one?

